## Naming Conventions

- **React components**: PascalCase (e.g., `AuthenticationPortal`, `EnvironmentSettings`)
- **Page components**: default export, PascalCase, end with `Page` (e.g., `AuthPage`)
- **File names**: match exported component in PascalCase (e.g., `AuthenticationPage.tsx`, `EnvironmentSettings.tsx`)
- **Directories**: kebab-case or Next.js conventions
  - Feature components live in `_components/` under their page folder
- **Functions/variables**: camelCase
- **Constants/enums**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- **Absolute imports only**: use `@/*` alias, never relative `../../..`
- **Icons/third-party**: import from package root and use PascalCase in JSX

